{
  "stem": "11964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But we also would be sent, my older sister and I would be sent to a-- it wasn't a camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We called it a pension in the mountains, in the Tatra Mountains and the Carpathian Mountains, where we would go for the summer.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And our parents would come to visit us on Parents' Day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They would sometimes vacation in an adult resort place called Krynica, and on the way they would visit with us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Later on, after Tobcia was born, who we call now Terry, we would go to a nearby place, which was sort of a-- a little country place, very, very nice, with a lot of forestry.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we would go there for the summer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my father would come for the weekend and commute.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We did not interact with any of the Gentile children, because the social intercourse was just not something that we could enter into.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father and my mother knew a lot of the Gentile people, because they were our customers, but there was no social contact.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Certainly neither would their parents, the Gentile parents, allow it, nor would we be comfortable with it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "For example, there were two men's high school, boys' high schools, which were non-Jewish, Gentile high schools, and one girls' high school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And none of the Jewish children would be allowed to enter these high schools.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in as much as there wasn't overt anti-Semitism, as far as somebody calling us names, we knew our place.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew that we couldn't enter into any kind of relationship.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That changed later on when I went for a very brief stint at the-- to the university in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the-- the Jewish community was very much a tight community, but it was a very Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
